  <title>How to get relative path of script or notebook in Python with Pathlib library</title>
  <dc:creator>Daniel Borek</dc:creator>
  <link>https://danielborek.me/posts/2021/03/til-relative-path-notebook/index.html</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 



<p><em>Problem statement</em>: You want to get an absolute path of your project where a file/notebook is located and join it with a string pointing to a folder.</p>
<p>Solution:</p>
<p>This function will give you an absolute path in relation to a current python script or notebook.</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb1" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode python code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode python"><span id="cb1-1"><span class="im" style="color: #00769E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">from</span> pathlib <span class="im" style="color: #00769E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">import</span> Path</span>
<span id="cb1-2"></span>
<span id="cb1-3"><span class="kw" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">def</span> get_project_root() <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">-&gt;</span> Path:</span>
<span id="cb1-4">    <span class="cf" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">try</span>:</span>
<span id="cb1-5">        <span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;"># This will give you a Path object pointing to the parent of the folder where the script is located.</span></span>
<span id="cb1-6">        <span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;"># If your script is `/root/scripts/script.py`, the result will be an absolute path '/root'.</span></span>
<span id="cb1-7">        <span class="cf" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">return</span> Path(<span class="va" style="color: #111111;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">__file__</span>).parent.parent</span>
<span id="cb1-8">    <span class="cf" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">except</span> <span class="pp" style="color: #AD0000;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">NameError</span> <span class="im" style="color: #00769E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">as</span> error:</span>
<span id="cb1-9">        <span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;"># This will give you  root folder of the project if this runned through jupyter notebook</span></span>
<span id="cb1-10">        <span class="cf" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">return</span> Path().joinpath().absolute().parents[<span class="dv" style="color: #AD0000;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">0</span>]</span>
<span id="cb1-11">    <span class="cf" style="color: #003B4F;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">except</span> <span class="pp" style="color: #AD0000;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">Exception</span> <span class="im" style="color: #00769E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">as</span> exception:</span>
<span id="cb1-12">        <span class="bu" style="color: null;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">print</span>(exception)</span></code></pre></div>
<p>When you will work with <code>Path</code> paths don’t add trailing slashes when joining paths. The code below:</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb2" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode python code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode python"><span id="cb2-1">root<span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">=</span> get_project_root()</span>
<span id="cb2-2">path_to_file <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">=</span> Path.joinpath(root, <span class="st" style="color: #20794D;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">'/data/data.feather'</span>)</span></code></pre></div>
<p>will result in <code>path_to_file = /data/final.feather</code>.</p>
<p>To obtain <code>path_to_file = /root/data/final.feather</code> you shouldn’t use the slash at the begining:</p>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb3" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode python code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode python"><span id="cb3-1">root<span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">=</span> get_project_root()</span>
<span id="cb3-2">path_to_file <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">=</span> Path.joinpath(root, <span class="st" style="color: #20794D;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">'data/data.feather'</span>)</span></code></pre></div>



 ]]></description>
